<TITLE> Body of CU student recovered </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com)  Police have recovered the body of a Chittagong University student from a rail crossing at Khillapara in the port city. The body was recovered on Monday but police were unable to identify the body until Tuesday as that of Harunur Rashid Kaiser, a third year student of the university's marketing department. Kaiser came from Raghabpur village of Mirsharai, Chittagong. Wounds were visible on his stomach and back, Hathazari police chief Gias Uddin told bdnews24.com. Those responsible for his death might have left the body on the rail crossing after killing him somewhere else, Gias said. Railway police chief Md Shahidullah said they had found the body shortly after 7am on Monday and have filed a case in connection with the incident. CU assistant proctor Chandan Kumar Dey said that the authorities had assigned the Criminal Investigation Department of police to investigate the matter. The university's vice chancellor Abu Yusuf said they would take all possible efforts to find the responsible criminals. Additional police have been deployed on the campus and the situation is under control, he said. b
